hondo717: But I love to make aggressive preempts in 3rd seat. Here is a good rule to follow when opening in 3rd seat. It turns out, after 2 passes, on average, the 2 passed hands hold 16 HCP which means that 3rd seat and 4th seat hold 24 HCP between them on average. If you subtract your HCP from 24 in 3rd seat you know approximately how many HCP 4th seat is likely to have. Here assuming East is going to pass, I would subtract my 6 HCP from 24 and figure that West has about 18 HCP on average. So I would want to make it as difficult as possible for the opponents. Therefore, despite only have 5 so-so hearts I would open a weak 2@H bid in 3rd seat.



 
 

 

 
